## Rules

### ARCH-001: Single Responsibility Principle
severity: ERROR
scope: all classes and modules
rule: Every class MUST have exactly one reason to change. Classes that mix business logic with infrastructure concerns MUST be refactored.
threshold: max_class_lines=150, max_responsibilities=1
example_correct: |
  class OrderProcessor:
      def process(self, order: Order) -> Result: ...

  class OrderRepository:
      def save(self, order: Order) -> None: ...
example_incorrect: |
  class OrderManager:
      def process(self, order: Order) -> Result: ...
      def save(self, order: Order) -> None: ...
      def send_email(self, order: Order) -> None: ...

### ARCH-002: Dependency Direction
severity: ERROR
scope: module imports and package structure
rule: Dependencies MUST flow inward: CLI → core → stdlib only. Core modules MUST NOT import from CLI or plugin layers. Circular dependencies are prohibited.
threshold: max_function_lines=30, max_class_lines=200
example_correct: |
  # src/specforge/core/service.py
  from pathlib import Path  # stdlib OK
example_incorrect: |
  # src/specforge/core/service.py
  from specforge.cli.main import cli  # MUST NOT import from CLI

### ARCH-003: Constructor Injection
severity: ERROR
scope: all service and handler classes
rule: All dependencies MUST be injected via the constructor. Global state and module-level singletons are prohibited.
threshold: max_constructor_params=5
example_correct: |
  class FileWriter:
      def __init__(self, fs: FileSystem) -> None:
          self._fs = fs
example_incorrect: |
  _FS = FileSystem()  # global — prohibited

  class FileWriter:
      def write(self, path: Path) -> None:
          _FS.write(path)
